The paper deals with complementation of finite automata on infinite words, which is a fundamental problem in automata theory and has applications in mathematical logic, model-checking, program analysis, and verification. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category, as the paper deals with a problem in mathematical logic. 

cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a likely sub-category, as the paper deals with complementation of finite automata. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible sub-category, as the paper presents upper bounds for the complexity of Streett and parity complementation. 

cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible sub-category, as the paper deals with program analysis and verification, which are related to programming languages. 

cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible sub-category, as the paper deals with the complexity of complementation of finite automata, which is a problem in computational complexity.
